##Grandma Wang's last Spring Festival in Wuhan

Southreviews

Functional presentation, the power of calm

On the morning of February 18, Wang Hong woke up early, shaken.

Around 6:20, news of her aunt Wang Bing came from the family group: The hospital called, they're still working on her, but the compressions aren't responding.

After 7:00, no calls. Did He make it? Wang Hong said, God bless, God bless.

At 7:50, finally the result: Aunt died, has been quickly cremated, after the epidemic, to pick up her ashes back.

"The sky is falling, " said Wang Bing's daughter-in-law in the crowd

Wang Hong, staring at the screen, broke down, hugged his son, and burst into tears.

Wang Hong and her aunt Wang Bing worked together for 15 years in the clinic at the gate of the Wudianyi community in Wuhan. The clinic was founded on the basis of the community. In 20 years, it has been the warmest link in the community. People Admire Dr. Wang for his high skill and good medical ethics, the patron saint of the neighborhood.

People Admire Dr. Wang Bing (left) high skill, good medical ethics, is the patron saint of the community

After the city was shut down, she continued to work late into the night with a surge of patients at a clinic for nearby residents. On New Year's Eve, she was still giving injections to patients, on the third day of the Lunar New Year, she also opened the door for patients to get medicine.

Wang Bing also served for 15 years as director of the community's property committee. On the eve of the Lunar New Year's Eve, she arranged for her children to go around buying protective and disinfectant supplies in an effort to help residents survive the outbreak, but on January 27, she and her family collapsed one after another, to be the only infected family in a community of over 400.

When news of Wang Bing's death came, the whole community was devastated.

"Granny Wang, help! "
In early January, when a suspected SARS virus appeared on the Internet in Wuhan, the masks at Wang Bing's medical clinic at the entrance to the Wudianyi community were out of stock, and Wang Bing went on to buy 200.

The masks were kept after officials soon announced that no human-to-human transmission had been detected. It was not until more than 10 days later that the danger of the outbreak was detected and masks were quickly sold out.

Wang Bing went to the big drug stores to buy, at this time, the mask has risen to a dollar, buy back, she sold at the original price. The mask she and her family used was bought online by her daughter-in-law at a high price.

Fever cases have surged since January. Normally, Wang Bing would send patients to the hospital for a checkup, and if it was the flu, he would recommend that they be treated there. The flu requires Oseltamivir, which is not available at her clinic. If it was the common cold, she told the patient, you can go back to the clinic injection, medicine.

At the time, people thought it was just the flu and didn't care too much, said Wang Hong, who works as an administrator at the Wang Bing Clinic. But on January 23, the city of Wuhan was sealed off, and the dark cloud of the epidemic finally weighed on everyone's mind.

Fever patients too many, many patients in the hospital queue for several days, also can not get treatment, have run back to the clinic, ask Dr. Wang for help. Wang Bing used to work from morning till late at night.

Wang Bing was the only doctor in the clinic, along with Wang Hong, an administrator, and Wang Hong's sister, a nurse who had been transferred from the army. Because the clinic was short-handed, my sister came to help early last year, and later she said she felt like a volunteer here.

Before the Spring Festival, Wang Hong and his sister went to the clinic, leaving only Wang Bing. What Wang Hong and her sister did not expect was that this parting would be forever.

On New Year's Eve, Wang Bing was still helping people with injections, the patient himself had not the heart, said to go to the hospital to try to see if can see a doctor. Wang Bing said, never mind, it's not easy, you come early, I give you fight, so as not to run in vain. After the injection, she went back to eat New Year's Eve dinner. By this time, most of the clinics were closed.

On the other hand, out of the doctor's sensitivity, coupled with the responsibility of the director of the Industry Committee, Wang Bing early response to the epidemic prevention and control. Just closed city, she went to work before a trip to the property, the purchase of infrared temperature gun, before the need to measure the body temperature, in and out to disinfection. In the evening, she organized industry committee overtime meeting to discuss prevention and control program.

Earlier than most neighborhoods in the neighborhood, Wang Bing mobilized people to clear the hallways, clean the trash cans, and tell the owners not to go downstairs.

New Year's Eve, she contacted everywhere, finally found in Caidian District the last few boxes of 84 disinfectant, the business has not shipped, Wang Bing asked his son to drive more than 40 kilometers back.

Instead of having dinner on New Year's Eve, at 10 p.m. , they went to the east West Lake Farm Machinery Market, which had already been closed for the holiday, contacted the executive manager, and bought two electric farm case sprayers, together with the few boxes of face masks they had, overnight the epidemic prevention materials sent to the Property Office.

They have two times, one by one on the corridor, security doors for disinfection, basically the entire community of 13 buildings are covered.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Wang Bing was still busy, the whole family advised her to take care of her health, she promised, but then a person went to the clinic.

She did not have the heart, so many patients are too poor, there are young patients begged "Wang Grandma, help" , the family said, encountered such a cry for help, her eyes were full of tears.

To the third day of the second day, as long as the residents of a telephone, even if it is a simple inquiry and medicine, she also immediately ran to open the door. At this point, she has no more protective material, wearing only a disposable medical mask.

It wasn't until the third day of the Lunar New Year, January 27, that her family persuaded her to stop seeing her daughter, who was far away in Singapore.

Born in 1947 at the age of 72, Wang Bing is still energetic, with short curly hair, a plump face, a pair of Red Phoenix eyes, and a smile that she uses to hail anyone who walks by.

Her legs were varicose veins, often swollen, an occupational hazard of a lifetime as a doctor.

In the impression of Xiong Qingqun, a resident, she was always "spinning, Spinning" in the clinic, refusing to sit down.

The old woman retained the fortitude, enthusiasm and vigour of a strong woman of her youth.

The doctor's suspension was too late to protect herself, and on the third day of the Lunar New Year, she developed symptoms such as a cold and fatigue. Her niece, Wang Hong, was certain that she had contracted it at the clinic. Because other than eating, other than the times she went to buy masks, she hardly went out on the street. She was in the clinic.

In order not to let the family worry, she also daily with the daughter of Singapore video report safe. But on January 31, she began to realize that it was a viral infection.

The hospital was already overcrowded and one bed was hard to find, with many people lining up in the cold. Family members said Wang Bing did not want to compete for the resources of critically ill patients, simply at home on their own infusion. At this point, she was unable to video-chat with her daughter.

The Grief Clinic
In 1960, when Wang Bing was 13 years old, she moved from Rural Xiangtan to study in Wuhan, joining her brother, Wang Hong, as her father. Wang Hong's impression of the aunt was that her handwriting was large, like a man's, as well as her name.

An outspoken aunt has a delicate side, too. Wang Bing was a good hook jumper, Wang Hong said. She knitted Wang Hong's father beautiful sweaters, and like her amazing stitching skills years later, she was too thin and thick to be a doctor.

Later, when Wang Bing was admitted to the nursing school affiliated to Hubei Medical College, she bragged to her family that she had read all the books in the Nursing School Library.

After graduation, Wang Bing went to a hospital in Xiaogan to become a nurse, then a head nurse.

Her husband, a teacher at the Wuhan Electric Power Institute, had to sacrifice her career to return to Wuhan after years of separation in order to reunite and raise her children. Then self-taught examination of a medical certificate, in the Wuhan Electric Power Instrument Factory Medical Office when the doctor for many years. Xiong Qingqun of electric instrument factory is very impressed with this colleague: "She is very good, medical ethics is high, internal medicine and surgery will be, many patients in the factory difficult disease, have been solved by her. "

Later, Wuhan Electric Power Instrument Factory restructuring, the doctors in the medical room one after another, leaving only a nurse. By this time Wang Bing, too, was retired and running a thriving tea house. Instrument factory workers once, still living together, maintaining a good neighborhood, they said, "Dr. Wang, you might as well open a clinic, but also convenient for everyone. "

Back in 2003, she opened a clinic in front of the Wudianyi community -- The medical clinic of King soldiers of the West in Hongshan District. In 2006, after Wang Hong was laid off, her aunt Wang Bing told her, "why don't you just work for me, " and she became an administrator at the clinic, where she remains today.

Dr. Wang Bing (center) poses with clinic staff

When Wang Hong was 17, her father left. "My sister and I have received a lot of favors from my aunt. When Times are difficult, my aunt often gives money and presents, and she is very willing to give it up. "

There was a time when Wang Hong had no one to take care of the children, so the aunt came every day to give them a bath, and went to work without leaving a day behind. In the early years, the aunt benefited from her family, now, the aunt has become the niece of "the right person" , they "like mother and daughter.

In Wang Hong's mind, my aunt was a good seamstress and a good healer. Once upon a time there was a woman in a Wuhan University Vegetable Farm who cut her meat with a knife. Her aunt gave her 27 stitches. A few months later, the patient came back, held out his hand, and there was no mark.

A patient came to the clinic with a heart attack. He got better after a simple rescue. The patient wanted to go back, but his aunt wouldn't let him go. His aunt, who had already left work, was still there, insisting that he ask her to bring her insurance card and rush her to the big hospital. The doctors there said it was too late, that it could be fatal.

The small clinic in Wudianyi district retains the warmth of the past time for the residents. "The medicine in the clinic can be taken apart and sold piecemeal, just like when we were kids in the clinic, " said a resident of Wudianyi community

A girl who often goes for injections in winter remembers that "granny Wang" would give her a hand-warmer every time. A migrant worker who used to live nearby got sick and took two trains from Dunkou to see Wang Bing. Not just because it's cheap, but because it's kind and trusting.

At the end of last year, a college student walked 20 minutes to the clinic after getting a stick stuck in his finger. Wang Bing picked it out with a needle and tweezers. I ended up charging 5 yuan for the tools. And the same wound, in the next second-class hospital, someone spent 300 yuan.

Industry Committee member Qi Xiaoming and residents laugh at her: "Don't you lose money? "

"It doesn't matter how much I earn, as long as everyone is well and I'm happy, I'll be a friend, " she said. Wang Bing also told Qi, "everyone who comes to see me looks up to me. " This made her feel that she was a sincere doctor, it's a high level.

When it came to the poor, Wang Bing took less money, or nothing at all. Patients in the community who have financial difficulties, she called for donations, and she is often the largest donation. She gives money to people who have died.

In 2005, Wang Bing was elected director of the Wu Dianyi community, an old, self governing community with a myriad of chores, trivialities and complications, but she was never bored. He remembers Wang Bing telling her that he would sometimes wake up in the middle of the night thinking about his community. In the early years, Wang Bing led the community to install natural gas pipelines, when the owners of the community is very controversial, some agree, some disagree, some are too expensive, Wang Bing family to talk, finally installed the pipeline.

Qi was under the impression that Wang Bing was keen to take part in all the activities in the community, big and small. She had bad legs, but she still wanted to dance. "It doesn't matter if I'm not a good dancer. I'll stand in the back, but I have to take part. Our spirit has to show. "

Qi said Wang Bing had called her when she became symptomatic, and had discussed hanging up a banner to warn people. But Wang Bing had no idea what was going to happen to her.

Bad News
The illness was overwhelming, and the urgency of the situation exceeded all expectations.

As Wang Bing grew weaker, his family took care of him day and night, making all kinds of phone calls, and Wang Hong called the Private Medical Association for help. There were still no hospitals.

On the morning of February 1, the family drove to Wuhan 672 hospital, "but they do not accept serious illness, only mild illness. ".

After that, the son had to drive to the army general hospital. There is no need to register at this time, the hospital directly to the shock of Wang Bing into the emergency room, the hospital issued a critical notice, the doctor directly to her hanging on the oxygen device. By this time, Wang Bing's lungs had turned white, and Oxygenation was at 60 percent, hanging by a thread.

But the doctors couldn't get her admitted, for the simple reason that there was no nucleic acid, no bed. And the doctor said if we don't find a hospital, we're not gonNA make it through the night. Family feel cold: "every day to save the doctor, seriously ill but can not be admitted to hospital. "

The community urgently reports to the streets and districts, but the process goes on, and in Live and Let Die, it is unquestionably long.

When the families posted their distress messages online, Drow found them and said they had been given a nucleic acid quota to do at a Hankou Hospital. But by then, Wang Bing had no energy or time to cope with the nucleic acid test.

Finally, the family found a bed at Caidian district people's Hospital, and at 1 a.m. on February 2, Wang Bing was hospitalized, using a suction machine.

Wang Bing's in the ambulance

It's after 8:00 in the morning. Doctor's appointment. Notify the family. Be Prepared. The doctor started with a three-day treatment plan. Wang Bing had a will to live and survived for three days, but the Oxygenation hadn't changed much.

In desperation, the doctor had to cut Wang Bing's trachea open, the establishment of artificial breathing, hanging on a vacuum cleaner, Wang Bing passed the critical period.

The next day, Wang Bing woke up and the nurse sent back a video from her cell phone showing her wearing a breathing machine and prying food out of her mouth with chopsticks. The family's heart dropped a little at last when they mentioned it in their throat. It was the last time Wang Hong saw her face.

The same day, the family bought 18 bottles of Immunoglobulin, and money to the man who sold the drug sent over. The doctor who was on duty in the hospital was from another province. He gave her six bottles that day.

Later, when Wang Hong called her aunt, Wang Bing told her niece, who was like her own daughter, "I'm hungry and I want to eat, " Wang Hong said, "Aunt, I'm sure you'll be all right. You must be strong and hold on, " Wang Bing replied in a weak voice. "MMM... " her voice was barely audible.

At this point, no one dared tell Wang Bing that her son and daughter in law had been quarantined in the hotel after they had taken her to hospital, where they were later found to have lung infections, her son was admitted to the hospital with a serious illness, and her daughter in law was transferred to a Shelter Hospital with a mild illness. At the same time, Wang Bing's in-laws in the New Year's mother, also confirmed in hospital. Wang Bing's husband and grandson were all that remained.

Wang Bing's situation, which had been stable for two days, took a turn for the worse, and she was transferred to the ICU, where for more than a dozen days, Wang Hong was unable to find out the details of her aunt's health.

It wasn't until Feb. 17 that her family informed her that her aunt had been unable to pass urine for kidney failure and needed a blood filter. Wang Bing, with a strong will to survive, is still struggling with the virus.

On the morning of February 18th, as if anticipating something, Wang Hong woke up at 6 am. Wang Bing was in the hospital, in the middle of an emergency. And then there's the opening scene.

Wang Bing was gone, and now he had to keep the news from Wang Bing's husband. That day, Wang Bing's daughter gave him a shot, telling him that he needed to prepare for his mother's death. The old man was in a hurry at home at the moment, anxious to know how his wife was doing.

The couple have been in love all their lives, and over the years, they have developed a relationship where the retired engineer, who cooks for his wife all year round, personally takes her to the clinic when she doesn't have time to go home. Wang Hong couldn't imagine what the news would do to the man in his 70s.

The only strategy the family discussed was to hope that the less symptomatic daughter-in-law would be discharged from the shelter hospital, return home, accompany the old man, and find another opportunity to tell him.

But on February 17th, she tested positive for nucleic acids. There's no telling when he'll be released.

On Feb. 19, the day after Wang Bing's death, the community formed a common understanding: everyone hid from him and waited for his family to return.

After graduation, Wang Bing went to a hospital in Xiaogan to become a nurse, then a head nurse.

Her husband, a teacher at the Wuhan Electric Power Institute, had to sacrifice her career to return to Wuhan after years of separation in order to reunite and raise her children. Then self-taught examination of a medical certificate, in the Wuhan Electric Power Instrument Factory Medical Office when the doctor for many years. Xiong Qingqun of electric instrument factory is very impressed with this colleague: "She is very good, medical ethics is high, internal medicine and surgery will be, many patients in the factory difficult disease, have been solved by her. "

Later, Wuhan Electric Power Instrument Factory restructuring, the doctors in the medical room one after another, leaving only a nurse. By this time Wang Bing, too, was retired and running a thriving tea house. Instrument factory workers once, still living together, maintaining a good neighborhood, they said, "Dr. Wang, you might as well open a clinic, but also convenient for everyone. "

Back in 2003, she opened a clinic in front of the Wudianyi community -- The medical clinic of King soldiers of the West in Hongshan District. In 2006, after Wang Hong was laid off, her aunt Wang Bing told her, "why don't you just work for me, " and she became an administrator at the clinic, where she remains today.

Dr. Wang Bing (center) poses with clinic staff

When Wang Hong was 17, her father left. "My sister and I have received a lot of favors from my aunt. When Times are difficult, my aunt often gives money and presents, and she is very willing to give it up. "

There was a time when Wang Hong had no one to take care of the children, so the aunt came every day to give them a bath, and went to work without leaving a day behind. In the early years, the aunt benefited from her family, now, the aunt has become the niece of "the right person" , they "like mother and daughter.

In Wang Hong's mind, my aunt was a good seamstress and a good healer. Once upon a time there was a woman in a Wuhan University Vegetable Farm who cut her meat with a knife. Her aunt gave her 27 stitches. A few months later, the patient came back, held out his hand, and there was no mark.

A patient came to the clinic with a heart attack. He got better after a simple rescue. The patient wanted to go back, but his aunt wouldn't let him go. His aunt, who had already left work, was still there, insisting that he ask her to bring her insurance card and rush her to the big hospital. The doctors there said it was too late, that it could be fatal.

The small clinic in Wudianyi district retains the warmth of the past time for the residents. "The medicine in the clinic can be taken apart and sold piecemeal, just like when we were kids in the clinic, " said a resident of Wudianyi community

A girl who often goes for injections in winter remembers that "granny Wang" would give her a hand-warmer every time. A migrant worker who used to live nearby got sick and took two trains from Dunkou to see Wang Bing. Not just because it's cheap, but because it's kind and trusting.

At the end of last year, a college student walked 20 minutes to the clinic after getting a stick stuck in his finger. Wang Bing picked it out with a needle and tweezers. I ended up charging 5 yuan for the tools. And the same wound, in the next second-class hospital, someone spent 300 yuan.

Industry Committee member Qi Xiaoming and residents laugh at her: "Don't you lose money? "

"It doesn't matter how much I earn, as long as everyone is well and I'm happy, I'll be a friend, " she said. Wang Bing also told Qi, "everyone who comes to see me looks up to me. " This made her feel that she was a sincere doctor, it's a high level.

When it came to the poor, Wang Bing took less money, or nothing at all. Patients in the community who have financial difficulties, she called for donations, and she is often the largest donation. She gives money to people who have died.

In 2005, Wang Bing was elected director of the Wu Dianyi community, an old, self governing community with a myriad of chores, trivialities and complications, but she was never bored. He remembers Wang Bing telling her that he would sometimes wake up in the middle of the night thinking about his community. In the early years, Wang Bing led the community to install natural gas pipelines, when the owners of the community is very controversial, some agree, some disagree, some are too expensive, Wang Bing family to talk, finally installed the pipeline.

Qi was under the impression that Wang Bing was keen to take part in all the activities in the community, big and small. She had bad legs, but she still wanted to dance. "It doesn't matter if I'm not a good dancer. I'll stand in the back, but I have to take part. Our spirit has to show. "

Qi said Wang Bing had called her when she became symptomatic, and had discussed hanging up a banner to warn people. But Wang Bing had no idea what was going to happen to her.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Bad News

The illness was overwhelming, and the urgency of the situation exceeded all expectations.

As Wang Bing grew weaker, his family took care of him day and night, making all kinds of phone calls, and Wang Hong called the Private Medical Association for help. There were still no hospitals.

On the morning of February 1, the family drove to Wuhan 672 hospital, "but they do not accept serious illness, only mild illness. ".

After that, the son had to drive to the army general hospital. There is no need to register at this time, the hospital directly to the shock of Wang Bing into the emergency room, the hospital issued a critical notice, the doctor directly to her hanging on the oxygen device. By this time, Wang Bing's lungs had turned white, and Oxygenation was at 60 percent, hanging by a thread.

But the doctors couldn't get her admitted, for the simple reason that there was no nucleic acid, no bed. And the doctor said if we don't find a hospital, we're not gonNA make it through the night. Family feel cold: "every day to save the doctor, seriously ill but can not be admitted to hospital. "

The community urgently reports to the streets and districts, but the process goes on, and in Live and Let Die, it is unquestionably long.

When the families posted their distress messages online, Drow found them and said they had been given a nucleic acid quota to do at a Hankou Hospital. But by then, Wang Bing had no energy or time to cope with the nucleic acid test.

Finally, the family found a bed at Caidian district people's Hospital, and at 1 a.m. on February 2, Wang Bing was hospitalized, using a suction machine.

Wang Bing's in the ambulance

It's after 8:00 in the morning. Doctor's appointment. Notify the family. Be Prepared. The doctor started with a three-day treatment plan. Wang Bing had a will to live and survived for three days, but the Oxygenation hadn't changed much.

In desperation, the doctor had to cut Wang Bing's trachea open, the establishment of artificial breathing, hanging on a vacuum cleaner, Wang Bing passed the critical period.

The next day, Wang Bing woke up and the nurse sent back a video from her cell phone showing her wearing a breathing machine and prying food out of her mouth with chopsticks. The family's heart dropped a little at last when they mentioned it in their throat. It was the last time Wang Hong saw her face.

The same day, the family bought 18 bottles of Immunoglobulin, and money to the man who sold the drug sent over. The doctor who was on duty in the hospital was from another province. He gave her six bottles that day.

Later, when Wang Hong called her aunt, Wang Bing told her niece, who was like her own daughter, "I'm hungry and I want to eat, " Wang Hong said, "Aunt, I'm sure you'll be all right. You must be strong and hold on, " Wang Bing replied in a weak voice. "MMM... " her voice was barely audible.

At this point, no one dared tell Wang Bing that her son and daughter in law had been quarantined in the hotel after they had taken her to hospital, where they were later found to have lung infections, her son was admitted to the hospital with a serious illness, and her daughter in law was transferred to a Shelter Hospital with a mild illness. At the same time, Wang Bing's in-laws in the New Year's mother, also confirmed in hospital. Wang Bing's husband and grandson were all that remained.

Wang Bing's situation, which had been stable for two days, took a turn for the worse, and she was transferred to the ICU, where for more than a dozen days, Wang Hong was unable to find out the details of her aunt's health.

It wasn't until Feb. 17 that her family informed her that her aunt had been unable to pass urine for kidney failure and needed a blood filter. Wang Bing, with a strong will to survive, is still struggling with the virus.

On the morning of February 18th, as if anticipating something, Wang Hong woke up at 6 am. Wang Bing was in the hospital, in the middle of an emergency. And then there's the opening scene.

Wang Bing was gone, and now he had to keep the news from Wang Bing's husband. That day, Wang Bing's daughter gave him a shot, telling him that he needed to prepare for his mother's death. The old man was in a hurry at home at the moment, anxious to know how his wife was doing.

The couple have been in love all their lives, and over the years, they have developed a relationship where the retired engineer, who cooks for his wife all year round, personally takes her to the clinic when she doesn't have time to go home. Wang Hong couldn't imagine what the news would do to the man in his 70s.

The only strategy the family discussed was to hope that the less symptomatic daughter-in-law would be discharged from the shelter hospital, return home, accompany the old man, and find another opportunity to tell him.

But on February 17th, she tested positive for nucleic acids. There's no telling when he'll be released.

On Feb. 19, the day after Wang Bing's death, the community formed a common understanding: everyone hid from him and waited for his family to return.
